            >
              <span slot="content">Peter &amp; John &amp; Elaine Oh My!

Slow build up but then it grabs you and you can&#39;t stop watching. Elaine May (mis)directed this film. The original release was incomprehensible due to the studio dumping it and washing its hands due to disagreement and frustrations with Elaine May, who wouldn&#39;t direct another film until Ishtar 11 years later. May had so much talent that went unused because she couldn&#39;t play with the studios. Back to this film, the final scene will haunt me for some time.

